27509bf6-6045-564a-bd22-603bf56afcf3,tg:rubgr:2391,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] The picture appeared in Sale Christie 29 June 1973, N°50 as from the Collection of Mr. & Mrs. Stanley Wulc of Rydal, Pennsylvania. Jan Brueghel the Elder 50. A Woody River Landscape with two hunstmen crossing, [...], on panel 14 3/4 x 21 1/2 in. (37,5 x 34,6). ""The attrib[ution] of this picture to Jan Brueghel the Elder is accepted by Dr. F. Grossmann (letter of 2 June 1968); and this picture is thus presumed to have been executed early in Jan's career. The same picture (or a version) appears in Jan Brueghel the Elder's Allegory of Sight (Prado, N° 1394) that is dated 1617; [blad 1, verso] [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. new observation (not communicated to anybody) (June 1973): Drawing in Albertina by J.B. extremely closer repr. in Article by T. Gerszi, in Jh.d. Berliner Museen, VII, 1965, Abb. 16, discussed p. 110; [blad 2, recto] Jan Brueghel: Landscape with Hunters. Another version with L. Koetser in exhibition 1972 or 1973.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] The picture appeared in Sale Christie 29 June 1973, N°50 as from the Collection of Mr. & Mrs. Stanley Wulc of Rydal, Pennsylvania. Jan Brueghel the Elder 50. A Woody River Landscape with two hunstmen crossing, [...], on panel 14 3/4 x 21 1/2 in. (37,5 x 34,6). ""The attrib[ution] of this picture to Jan Brueghel the Elder is accepted by Dr. F. Grossmann (letter of 2 June 1968); and this picture is thus presumed to have been executed early in Jan's career. The same picture (or a version) appears in Jan Brueghel the Elder's Allegory of Sight (Prado, N° 1394) that is dated 1617; [blad 1, verso] [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. new observation (not communicated to anybody) (June 1973): Drawing in Albertina by J.B. extremely closer repr. in Article by T. Gerszi, in Jh.d. Berliner Museen, VII, 1965, Abb. 16, discussed p. 110; [blad 2, recto] Jan Brueghel: Landscape with Hunters. Another version with L. Koetser in exhibition 1972 or 1973.</content>

<related_object.title>Stanley S. Wulc Sale, Christie's, June 29, 1973, illustrated, Lot 50. See my notes in catalogue. Another, better, version with L. Koetser, in Spring exh. 1970, N° 19 and again Spring 1972 (N° 36). A comparable drawing by J.B. (Albertina) published by T. Gerszi in Jb. Berliner Museen.</related_object.title>

<related_object.title>4 zw/w foto's. [Foto 1, geheel] [Handschrift onbekend]: '55,5 x 38,6 cm panneau'; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. van Leegenhoek, Mr. S.S. WULC, 1027 Washington Lane, Rydal, Pennsylvania 19046. Sold at Christie's 1973. By the same hand as the Lugt-Arndtgroup? Another version, very close, exh. Leonard Koetser London, Spring Exh. 1970, N° 19 as P. Brueghel the Younger, Panel 37,6 x 58,7 cm (143/4 x 23 in.) said to have been sold about a year earlier from a Canadian Collector at Sotheby's, cleaned by Rees-Jones= the same as version with Leonard Koetser 1972 (Spring exh. April-May, N° 36, repr. in colour), panel, 141/8 x 231/8 in. (37,7 x 58,6 cm) as P.B.II, but obviously Jan B. (great differences in foliage). Cf. Jan Brueghel, Forest Landscape with Robbers, Warsaw, exh. [Jan Bialostocki e.a.], Europ. Ldschfts Malerei 1550-1650 [= Europäische Landschaftsmalerei, 1550-1650], Dresden 1972, N°17, with the later foliage! Owl in tree near left border; [Foto 2, geheel] [Handschrift onbekend]: 'Dimensions en cm 55,5 x 38,5'; 2 detailfoto's.</related_object.title>

<related_object.title>Korte inhoud: Stuurt kleurenfoto van een werk van Jean Brueghel [sic], Landscape with Hunters and Dogs. Het werk behoort tot zijn collectie van XVI en XVII meesters. Werd door Dr. Michael Jaffé (Cambridge University) op de hoogte gebracht van FG. Jaffé nam contact op met Wulc n.a.v. de Jacob Jordaens tentoonstelling in Canada [= Ottawa]. Uitnodiging om de collectie, in Pennsylvania, te bezoeken.</related_object.title>
